  "text": "A total of 10,000 snapshots of the models in the simulations were used for further clustering analysis by the K-means cluster algorithm [CITATION_1] . Clustering analysis was performed in order to obtain the representative structures for each UC781/CD inclusion complexe (UC781/βCD, UC781/MβCD, and UC781/HPβCD). The clustering trajectory frames were categorized into ten groups based on trajectory similarity considered by the root mean square deviation (RMSD), comparing the backbone atoms of CD and UC781. The highest populated clustering trajectory among the ten groups was chosen to be a representative structure of each UC781/CD inclusion complex in this study.",
